.TH BNM3 1 "January 2025" "1.0.3" "BoredNoMore3 Manual"
.SH NAME
bnm3 \- graphical interface for BoredNoMore3 wallpaper manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bnm3
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bnm3
provides a professional CustomTkinter interface for managing the BoredNoMore3
wallpaper changer. It features real-time process control, console monitoring,
and configuration management.
.PP
The GUI spawns the backend daemon (borednomore3) as a subprocess and captures
its output in real-time, allowing users to monitor transitions, debug issues,
and control wallpaper rotation without touching configuration files or using
command-line arguments.
.PP
The interface includes a mission control style dashboard with sidebar controls,
tabbed settings panel, live console output, and advanced configuration options.
.SH FEATURES
.SS Process Management
.IP \(bu 2
START: Spawns backend daemon with configured parameters
.IP \(bu 2
STOP: Sends SIGHUP for graceful shutdown (5 second timeout, then SIGKILL)
.IP \(bu 2
FORCE KILL: Immediately sends SIGKILL to process group
.IP \(bu 2
Cleanup: Searches for and kills orphaned borednomore3.py processes using pgrep
.IP \(bu 2
Status display: Shows running/stopped state and process PID
.SS Live Console
.IP \(bu 2
Real-time stdout/stderr capture from backend process
.IP \(bu 2
Auto-scroll with color-coded timestamps
.IP \(bu 2
Export to file for troubleshooting
.IP \(bu 2
Console auto-clears at 1000 lines to prevent memory issues
.IP \(bu 2
Thread-safe output handling
.SS Configuration Management
.IP \(bu 2
All borednomore3 command-line parameters available via GUI controls
.IP \(bu 2
File path configuration: script path, config file, wallpaper directory, pattern list
.IP \(bu 2
Timing controls: interval, transition frames, frame delay speed
.IP \(bu 2
Transition selection: specific IDs or ranges (e.g., 1-10,50-60)
.IP \(bu 2
Behavior toggles: randomize transitions, randomize wallpapers, debug mode, keep image
.IP \(bu 2
State persistence: automatically saves and restores all settings between sessions
.SS Theme Support
Light, Dark, and System theme modes with instant switching. Theme preference
is saved and restored automatically.
