.SH PROCESS CONTROL DETAILS
.TP
.B Process Group Creation
Uses os.setsid() (Unix) to create independent process groups, allowing
clean signal handling and subprocess management.
.TP
.B Signal Handling
SIGHUP: Graceful shutdown request, waits 5 seconds for clean exit
.br
SIGKILL: Force termination if SIGHUP fails or FORCE KILL is used
.TP
.B Zombie Process Cleanup
Uses pgrep to find all borednomore3.py processes and terminates them
using SIGKILL to prevent resource leaks.
.TP
.B Output Capture
Spawns separate thread to read subprocess stdout/stderr in real-time
without blocking the GUI event loop.
